[0.017, "o", "\u001b[H\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \u001b[1;38;2;255;68;68mgodshell❯ \u001b[0m\u001b[38;2;204;204;204mNo, I'm not stuck. I just returned the PID 269299, which is an asciinema process that's been running for 19 hours\u001b[m   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mand is likely the one you want to kill. The other PIDs in the search results are either unrelated processes that happen to\u001b[m    \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mhave \"asciinema\" in their file effects, or are children of the main asciinema process. \u001b[0m                                       \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m\u001b[0m                                                                                                                              \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mIf you want to kill it, you can use:\u001b[0m                                                                                          \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m```bash\u001b[0m                                                                                                                       \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mkill 269299\u001b[0m                                                                                                                   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m```\u001b[0m                                                                                                                           \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mor if it doesn't respond:\u001b[0m                                                                                                     \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m```bash\u001b[0m                                                                                                                       \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204mkill -9 269299\u001b[0m                                                                                                                \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;204;204;204m```\u001b[0m                                                                                                                           \u001b[K\r\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \u001b[1;38;2;0;255;136m❯ \u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;240ma\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;240msk godshell something...\u001b[0m                                                                                                   \u001b[K\r\n \u001b[38;2;85;85;85mCtrl+([r]efresh [s]ave [l]oad [p]anel) type help for more info, Esc to toggle focus\u001b[0m                                           \u001b[K\r\n                                                                                                                               \u001b[K\u001b[J\u001b[33;H"]
